Congratulations, you have completed the Elyra AIDevSecOps tutorial!

In completing this tutorial, you have been guided through an end-to-end data science workflow aided by AICoE tools.

You started with either Project Meteor or Operate First to deploy your own JupyterHub instance, launch notebook images with Jupyter tooling and leverage Project Thoth bots to intelligently manage your dependencies. With your notebooks running, Elyra JupyterLab extensions supported your AI projects with add-ons such as Kubeflow Pipelines for end-to-end experiments. Finally, you deployed your model as a Flask application, and set up monitoring using Prometheus and Grafana.

Looking for more AICoE content? Check out the Operate First YouTube channel to see the latest updates for projects, find guided walkthroughs of notebooks, and learn best practices for Data Scientists and DevSevOps Engineers alike!
